org.daisy.pipeline.braille.common

Class BrailleCode

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.daisy.pipeline.braille.common.BrailleCode

  • public class BrailleCode
extends Object
    Identification of a braille system, including details on contraction levels, specialized braille systems, and additional elements relevant to braille production. For more info see the eBraille Braille Codes Registry.

      • toLanguageTag

        public Locale toLanguageTag(Locale sourceLanguage)
        Return a IETF BCP 47 language tag with the braille code identifier integrated as a "t" (transformed content) extension (RFC 6497) with a "x0" (private use transform) part.
        Parameters:
        sourceLanguage - The language tag of the source (untransformed) content.
        Returns:
        the language tag of the braille content, which contains the "Brai" script subtag and the braille code as a "t" extention.

      • fromLanguageTag

        public static BrailleCode fromLanguageTag(Locale language)
                                   throws IllegalArgumentException
        Get braille code from a IETF BCP 47 language tag. The language tag is expected to contain a "t" extension (RFC 6497) with a "x0" (private use transform) part, and the subtags after the "x0" subtag are expected to form the identifier of the braille code.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException
